TI  - The Industrial Structure of U.S. Direct Investment in the U.K.
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 5
EP  - 13
VL  - 7
IS  - 2
AB  - This paper evaluates alternative explanations of the industrial structure of U.S. Direct Investment in the U.K. on a cross-sectional basis, using multiple regression analysis. The most successful approach, in terms of explanatory power, is that based on industrial organization theory, although useful adjuncts are found in the market servicing approach and traditional investment determinants.
