PY  - 1976
DA  - 1976/06/01
TI  - Risk Reduction by International Diversification
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 75
EP  - 80
VL  - 7
IS  - 2
AB  - It is possible for multinational firms to reduce the risk of their profits by engaging in foreign operations (F/T). Empirical tests show that the (F/T) variable is inversely related to risk after allowing for size, industry classification, and other factors. This implies that international diversification offers to a multinational firm significant risk reduction advantages that are not available to a nonmultinational.
SN  - 1478-6990
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1057/palgrave.jibs.8490702
